#Thermal pollution
higher temperature of water decreases oxygen content (reduced solubility)
warmed water is less dense and floats on top, affecting whole water column
causes dead of fish and other organisms

Tidal bore: edge of tidal wave travels up against river current
- Qiantang River: Silver Dragon bore, largest
- Amazon River: Pororoca

Great Atlantic Sargassum Belt: recurring macroalgae bloom, from West Africa to Gulf of Mexico
- nutritients from Amazon river and West Africa upwelling currents
